<subSubSection pageId="202" pageNumber="806" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="202.[781,1375,294,717]" pageId="202" pageNumber="806">
<taxonomicName box="[783,930,412,441]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Hylomyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="202" pageNumber="806" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hylomyscus</taxonomicName>
heinrichorum is in the H. anselli species group (with anselli, kerbispeterhanst, and arcimontensis) based on absence of pectoral mammae but distinguished from other members of the group based on morphometric characters. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
